The higher education sector is expected to brief the media about measures to save the 2020 academic year and preparations for the next one. The academic year was disrupted by the Covid-19 lockdown. PRETORIA - Higher Education, Science and Innovation Minister, Dr Blade Nzimande will host a media briefing. Nzimande will announce further measures that will be implemented on COVID-19 in the sector. READ: COVID-19: No university is at high risk, says Nzimande The academic year has been disrupted by the COVID-19 pandemic and the nationwide lockdown. 